title: Loss to Mexico punctuates a rough year for US soccer
text: Photo: Jae C. Hong, AP United States's Bobby Woods, center, leaves the pitch after the CONCACAF Cup soccer match at the Rose Bowl Stadium, in Pasadena , Calif. Saturday, Oct. 10, 2015, The US team lost 2-3 to Mexico. United States's Bobby Woods, center, leaves the pitch after the... PASADENA, Calif. (AP) — The American Outlaws and their fellow U.S. soccer fans were louder, rowdier and more numerous than they were four years ago for their team's last clash with Mexico at the Rose Bowl.
